<inglise> COUNCIL DECISION of 26 June 1991 setting up a programme of options specific to the remote and insular nature of the Canary Islands (Poseican) (91/314/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU OTSUS nr 91/314/EM&Uuml;, millega kehtestatakse Kanaari saarte k&otilde;rvalisele asukohale ning saarelisele asendile vastavate valikmeetmete programm (Poseican) 26. juuni 1991 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91 of 26 June 1991 on the application of the provisions of Community law to the Canary Islands (1), and in particular Article 9 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 26. juuni 1991. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1911/91, mis k&auml;sitleb &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse s&auml;tete kohaldamist Kanaari saarte suhtes, (1) eriti selle artiklit 9, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the amended proposal from the Commission (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni muudetud ettepanekut, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (4), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (4) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Canary Islands suffer from a serious structural lack of development aggravated by a number of constraints (insular nature, remoteness, small size, difficult terrain and climate) whose unchanging nature and combined impact have serious effects on their economic and social development; whereas these special constraints make it necessary to step up Community support in order to ensure that the Canary Islands are fully involved in the dynamic of the internal market; whereas this Community support takes the form of operations under the reformed Structural Funds (enjoying the priority given to the Objective 1 regions), but must also ensure that the special constraints affecting the Canary Islands are taken into account in the application of common policies, in accordance with the Community approach to the remoter regions, of which the adoption and implementation of the Poseidom programme for the French overseas departments is the first practical example; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: Kanaari saarte t&otilde;sist strukturaalset mahaj&auml;&auml;must raskendavate piirangute (saareline asend, k&otilde;rvaline asukoht, v&auml;iksus, halvad maastiku- ja ilmastikuolud) muutumatu iseloom ja &uuml;hine toime m&otilde;jutavad t&otilde;siselt saarte majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset arengut; nende eriliste piirangute t&otilde;ttu on vaja intensiivistada &uuml;henduse abi, et tagada Kanaari saarte t&auml;ielik kaasamine siseturu d&uuml;naamilisse arengusse; &uuml;henduse abi antakse reformitud struktuurifondide raames (vastavalt eesm&auml;rgi 1 piirkondade eelistele), kuid samuti tuleb tagada, et &uuml;histe poliitikate kohaldamisel arvestatakse Kanaari saari m&otilde;jutavaid erilisi piiranguid vastavalt &uuml;henduse poliitikale k&otilde;rvalisemate piirkondade suhtes, millest programmi Poseidom vastuv&otilde;tmine ja rakendamine Prantsuse &uuml;lemeredepartemangude suhtes on esimene praktiline n&auml;ide; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas to achieve this, the Council, pursuant to Article 9 of Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91, must adopt a multi-sector programme of operations involving legislative measures and financial commitments to allow for the special constraints on the Canary Islands in the application of common policies; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu tuleb n&otilde;ukogul vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1911/91 artiklile 9 v&otilde;tta vastu mitmeid sektoreid h&otilde;lmav tegevuskava, mis sisaldab seadusandlikke meetmeid ja finantskohustusi, et v&otilde;tta &uuml;histe poliitikate kohaldamisel arvesse Kanaari saarte erilisi piiranguid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the purposes of implementing this programme, the necessary legal acts will be adopted either by the Council or by the Commission, as appropriate, before 31 December 1992; whereas the duration of the application of the measures to be adopted could, in certain cases, be linked to the process of strengthening the integration of the Canary Islands into common policies, or extend beyond this process, given the permanent constraints which are a particular feature of the Canary Islands; </inglise>
<eesti> selle programmi rakendamiseks v&otilde;tab n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i komisjon vastu vajalikud &otilde;igusaktid enne 31. detsembrit 1992; v&otilde;etavate meetmete kohaldamise kestus v&otilde;ib teatavatel juhtudel olla seotud protsessiga, millega tugevdatakse Kanaari saarte integreerimist &uuml;histesse poliitikatesse, v&otilde;i Kanaari saarte erijooneks olevaid p&uuml;sivaid piiranguid arvestades ulatuda selle protsessi j&auml;rgsesse aega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this programme must be based on the twofold principle that the Canary Islands form an integral part of the Community and that the regional reality deriving from their particular geographical situation and their historical economic and fiscal system must be recognized; </inglise>
<eesti> selle programmi aluseks on p&otilde;him&otilde;te, et Kanaari saared on &uuml;henduse lahutamatu osa ja et nende erilisest geograafilisest asendist tulenevaid piirkondlikke tingimusi ning ajaloolist majandus- ja fiskaals&uuml;steemi tuleb aktsepteerida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for this reason, the special measures laid down by the programme of operations must be part of the process of including the Canary Islands in the customs territory of the Community and extending to these Islands other provisions of Community law as stipulated in Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91; whereas these measures must accordingly take into account the special characteristics and constraints of the Canary Islands without undermining the integrity and coherence of the Community legal order; whereas the economic effects of specific measures must remain limited to the territory of the Canary Islands without affecting directly the functioning of the common market; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu peavad tegevusprogrammis s&auml;testatud erimeetmed olema osa protsessist, millega Kanaari saared liidetakse &uuml;henduse tolliterritooriumiga ja neile laiendatakse &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse teisi s&auml;tteid vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 1911/91; need meetmed peavad arvestama Kanaari saarte erijooni ja piiranguid, kahjustamata &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguskorra terviklikkust ja sidusust; erimeetmete majanduslik toime peab seet&otilde;ttu piirduma Kanaari saarte territooriumiga, ilma et see m&otilde;jutaks otseselt &uuml;histuru toimimist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Community rules must take account of the specific nature of the Canary Islands and permit their economic and social development, particularly in those areas where the fragile nature of island territories is particularly acute, such as transport, taxation, the social sector, research and development, or the protection of the environment in view of the vulnerability of the Canary Islands to the increasing pressures of tourism; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduse eeskirjad peavad arvestama Kanaari saarte erijooni ja v&otilde;imaldama nende majanduslikku ja sotsiaalset arengut, eelk&otilde;ige valdkondades, kus saarte &otilde;rn loodus on eriti kergesti haavatav, nagu transport, maksustamine, sotsiaalsektor, uurimis- ja arendustegevus v&otilde;i keskkonnakaitse, arvestades Kanaari saarte ohustatust suureneva turismi t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the exceptional geographical situation of the Canary Islands in relation to sources of supply for products used as inputs in certain food sectors, which are essential for current consumption or processing in the archipelago, entails costs that are a severe handicap for this area; whereas there is a need, in this connection, to make special arrangements for the supply of these products within the limits of local market needs and taking accunt of local production and traditional trade flows; </inglise>
<eesti> Kanaari saarte erandlik geograafiline asend teatavate saarestiku tarbimis- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisvajaduste rahuldamiseks h&auml;davajalike toiduainetesektorite toodete tarneallikate suhtes p&otilde;hjustab kulutusi, mis seavad k&otilde;nealused sektorid t&otilde;sisesse ebasoodsasse olukorda; seoses sellega on vaja kehtestada erikord nende toodete tarnimiseks turuvajaduste piires, v&otilde;ttes arvesse kohalikku toodangut ja tavap&auml;raseid kaubavoogusid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the same reasons and as part of the phased introduction of the Common Customs Tariff, there is a need to create the possibility of special tariff or derogations from the common commercial policy for certain sensitive products, in particular with regard to quantitative restrictions, bearing in mind the free-trade historical regime of the Canary Islands; whereas customs arrangements may also prove to be appropriate for the regime applicable to the Canary Islands' free zones; </inglise>
<eesti> samadel p&otilde;hjustel ja &uuml;hise tollitariifistiku j&auml;rkj&auml;rgulise kehtestamise osana on vaja luua eritariifi v&otilde;imalus v&otilde;i s&auml;testada teatavate tundlike toodete puhul erandid &uuml;hisest kaubanduspoliitikast, eelk&otilde;ige koguseliste piirangute osas, pidades silmas Kanaari saarte ajaloolist vabakaubanduskorda; tollikorraldus v&otilde;ib osutuda asjakohaseks Kanaari saarte vabatsoonide suhtes kohaldatava korra puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the special production conditions in the Canary Islands require that particular attention be paid to applying the common agricultural policy to this region; whereas appropriate measures are needed to assist the development of the fruit and vegetable and flowers and live plant sectors; whereas these measures will have to promote the growing of tropical products in particular; whereas it will also be necessary to introduce other measures to support domestic production intended for local consumption; </inglise>
<eesti> Kanaari saarte eriliste tootmistingimuste t&otilde;ttu on vaja p&ouml;&ouml;rata erilist t&auml;helepanu &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika kohaldamisele selles piirkonnas; on vaja kohaseid meetmeid, et aidata kaasa puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljasektori ning lillede ja elustaimede sektori arengule; need meetmed peavad eelk&otilde;ige soodustama troopikasaaduste kasvatamist; omamaiseks tarbimiseks m&otilde;eldud omamaise toodangu toetamiseks on vaja v&otilde;tta ka muid meetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas certain flanking measures are required to accompany the application of the common fisheries policy to the Canary Islands in order to take account of the particular features of local production; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;hise kalanduspoliitika kohaldamiseks Kanaari saarte suhtes on kohaliku tootmise erip&auml;ra arvestamiseks vaja teatavaid k&otilde;rvalmeetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the preparation, implementation, monitoring and evaluation of the measures provided for by its programme require a partnership between the Commission and the competent national and regional authorities; whereas this partnership must permit complementarity between the measures laid down in the programme and those applied at national and regional level; </inglise>
<eesti> selle programmiga etten&auml;htud meetmete ettevalmistamiseks, rakendamiseks, j&auml;relevalveks ja hindamiseks on vaja komisjoni ning p&auml;devate riiklike v&otilde;i piirkondlike asutuste koost&ouml;&ouml;d; see koost&ouml;&ouml; peab v&otilde;imaldama programmis s&auml;testatud meetmete ning riiklikul ja piirkondlikul tasandil v&otilde;etud meetmete vastastikust t&auml;iendavust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the competent national and regional authorities must take account of the measures and operations under this programme in drafting future regional development plans; whereas the Commission, within the scope of its powers, will take steps to ensure that this programme is consistent with the operations of the Structural Funds and other Community financial instruments, </inglise>
<eesti> p&auml;devad riiklikud ja piirkondlikud asutused peavad tulevaste piirkondlike arengukavade koostamisel v&otilde;tma arvesse k&auml;esoleva programmi meetmeid ja toiminguid; komisjon astub oma p&auml;devuse piires samme, et tagada k&auml;esoleva programmi vastavus struktuurifondide ja &uuml;henduse muude finantsvahenditega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS DECIDED AS FOLLOWS: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD J&Auml;RGMISE OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Pursuant to Article 9 of Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91, an action programme for the Canary Islands (Programme of options specific to the remote and insular nature of the Canary Islands), hereinafter referred to as the 'Poseican programme' and set out in the Annex, is hereby established. </inglise>
<eesti> Kanaari saarte jaoks kehtestatakse tegevusprogramm Poseican (Kanaari saarte k&otilde;rvalisele asukohale ning saarelisele asendile vastavate valikmeetmete programm), mis on s&auml;testatud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> This programme shall cover legislative measures and financial commitments. </inglise>
<eesti> See programm h&otilde;lmab seadusandlikke meetmeid ja finantskohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Within the context of the powers conferred upon it by the Treaty, the Council shall adopt the provisions necessary for the execution of this programme and invite the Commission to submit the relevant proposals as soon as possible. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;tab talle asutamislepinguga antud volituste raames vastu selle programmi teostamiseks vajalikud s&auml;tted ja kutsub komisjoni &uuml;les esitama v&otilde;imalikult kiiresti asjakohaseid ettepanekuid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The financial resources required to implement the measures relating to agricultural structures appearing in this programme shall be determined in the annual budgetary procedures. </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;llumajandusstruktuuridega seotud ja selles programmis nimetatud meetmete rakendamise rahalised vahendid m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks iga-aastase eelarvemenetluse raames. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall take effect on 1 July 1991. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus j&otilde;ustub 1. juulil 1991. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision shall be published in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus avaldatakse Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
